<p>I regard the similarity between AR and CotBG (specifically Cogwork Orthodoxy) to be the focus on machinery and robotics-based technology. Since the gentlemen below brought up PL, the difference is clear: PL is a broad contender who tries all, while AR (obviously) specialises in the specific domain of anomalous robotics.</p>
<p>Of course, one could easily say that CotBG applies religious meaning to the machine whereas AR applies business potential to it. Of which, the business angle is fairly covered by the PL format and MC&amp;D.</p>

