														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2504494">
									

<p>To put it another way, AR is in it for the science and the profit, sort of like their former competitor, Prometheus Labs. Where PL went under due to bad management, over-diversification, and over-investment in large projects with major flaws, Anderson Robotics is a smaller, more focused company that keeps their sights set just slightly beyond what's actually possible. The CotBG are among their major customers, but the difference is sort of like the difference between a wine maker and a Christian denomination that uses wine for communion.</p>

