				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/scorpion451" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1918720); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1918720&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610183482" alt="Scorpion451" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1918720)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/scorpion451" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1918720); return false;" >Scorpion451</a></span> <span class="odate time_1462663364 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">07 May 2016 23:22</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2505072">
									

<p>Even the &quot;blew themselves up&quot; part isn't necessarily a sign of incompetence:The <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/PEPCON_disaster">PEPCON disaster</a>, for instance, involved one of the US government's trusted producers of solid rocket fuel, which had been competently handling some of the most volatile substances on Earth for decades. They're still not entirely sure what set it off<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-979708-1" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-979708-1')">1</a></sup> but the end result was a series of some of the most energetic uncontrolled chemical explosions in recorded history, approximately 1 kiloton TNT equivalent.</p>
<div class="footnotes-footer">
<div class="title">Footnotes</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-979708-1"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-979708-1')">1</a>. getting forced by the government into storing literal tons more Ammonium Perchlorate than their facilities were designed to, the local gas company deciding that &quot;poorly maintained high pressure gas main&quot; and &quot;limited flow pipe&quot; were basically the same thing, and workers having no choice but to repair critical structural damage from a windstorm by welding near the storage area all may have played a part.</div>
</div>

							</div>

								
