			<div class="content" id="post-content-2510807">
									

<p>Alright, so the &quot;Investigative Timeline&quot; tab was rather bare bones, so it has been replaced by a tab for Gamma-13, the MTF that has been a major group in a lot of Anderson tales and articles. The investigative timeline is still found in that tab.</p>
<p>Special thanks again to <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/sunnyclockwork" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1621343); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1621343&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1463552570" alt="SunnyClockwork" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1621343)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/sunnyclockwork" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1621343); return false;">SunnyClockwork</a></span> for creating the MTF logo, making this page 100% more beautiful.</p>
<p>Lastly, Greenwolf's new tale, <a href="/the-analog-kid">The Analog Kid</a> has been added to that time line due to its importance in several upcoming tales.</p>
<p>Enjoy the pie.</p>

