					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/jacob-conwell" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1372582); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1372582&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610183482" alt="Jacob Conwell" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1372582)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/jacob-conwell" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1372582); return false;" >Jacob Conwell</a></span> <span class="odate time_1463558941 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">18 May 2016 08:09</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2510831">
									

<p>Currently I would argue that the GoI and the canon are not any more tied together than MC&amp;D is tied to any of the canons it appears in. Authors are free to use AR inside canons, outside canons, upside canons, and downside canons, and all relations to canons between.</p>
<p>The timeline on the final tab is merely the chronological order for the over arcing plot shared by the majority of AR tales, and should be seen no more as the end all be all version of AR than Resurrection is the end all be all story for this wiki.</p>

